<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="fr">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title></title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">
    <div class="box b1">
        <img src="historique.web.jpg">
        <h1>The History of Web Development</h1>
        <p>Web development started in the early 1990s with the creation of the World Wide Web.
           HTML was the first language used to build simple web pages. Later, CSS was introduced to improve design,
           and JavaScript was added to make websites interactive.Over time, web technologies have evolved 
           significantly, allowing developers to create complex and powerful web applications used in everyday life.</p>
        <button>read more...</button>
    </div>
    <div class="box b2">
        <img src="web.logo.png">
        <h1>Why Choose HTML, CSS, and JavaScript</h1>
        <p>HTML, CSS, and JavaScript are the core technologies of web development. 
          They are supported by all web browsers and are essential for building any website.Using these languages 
          ensures compatibility, flexibility, and performance. Unlike other programming languages, they are 
          specifically designed for the web, making them the best choice for creating modern websites.</p>
        <button>read more...</button>
    </div>
    <div class="box b3">
        <img src="html.logo.jpg">
        <h1>Introduction to HTML</h1>
        <p>HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the standard language used to create web pages. 
          It provides the basic structure of a website by organizing content into elements such as headings, 
          paragraphs, images, and links. HTML is easy to learn and is the first step for anyone who wants to
          enter the world of web development.Web programming using HTML allows developers to create structured
          and accessible websites. It is essential because every website on the internet is built using HTML 
          as a foundation.</p>
        <button>read more...</button>
    </div>
    <div class="box b4">
        <img src="css.logo.png">
        <h1>The Role of CSS in Web</h1>
        <p>CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is used to style and design web pages. While HTML provides the structure, 
          CSS controls the appearance, including colors, fonts, layouts, and spacing.CSS makes websites more 
          attractive and user-friendly. It also allows developers to create responsive designs that adapt to 
          different screen sizes such as mobile phones and tablets.</p>
        <button>read more...</button>
    </div>
    <div class="box b5">
        <img src="js.logo.png">
        <h1>JavaScript and Interactivity</h1>
        <p>JavaScript is a programming language that adds interactivity to websites. It allows developers to 
          create dynamic features such as animations, form validation, and real-time updates.With JavaScript,
           websites become more engaging and interactive. It works together with HTML and CSS to create complete
            and modern web applications.</p>
        <button>read more...</button>
    </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
